{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ghost|type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Drifloon}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ghost|prevnum=424|prev=Ambipom|nextnum=426|next=Drifblim|round=none}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Drifloon}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Drifloon\n|jname=フワンテ\n|tmname=Fuwante\n|ndex=425\n|sdex=065\n|u2dex=208\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=001\n|adex=064\n|abrow=142\n|obrow=232\n|opbrow=219\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Ghost\n|type2=Flying\n|category=Balloon\n|height-ftin=1\'04"\n|height-m=0.4\n|weight-lbs=2.6\n|weight-kg=1.2\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Aftermath\n|ability2=Unburden\n|abilityd=Flare Boost\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Amorphous\n|eggcycles=30\n|evtotal=1\n|evhp=1\n|expyield=70\n|oldexp=127\n|lv100exp=1,640,000\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Purple\n|catchrate=125\n|body=04\n|pokefordex=drifloon\n|generation=4\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Drifloon\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'フワンテ\'\'\' \'\'Fuwante\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Ghost|Flying}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation IV]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolve]]s into {{p|Drifblim}} starting at [[level]] 28.\n\n==Biology==\n[[File:Fantina Drifloon.png|thumb|left|220px|Drifloon\'s mouth, in the middle of the "X"]]\nDrifloon has a spherical, purple body with two stringy arms that have yellow, heart-shaped hands on the ends of them. At the base of its body is a frayed protrusion that resembles the tied end of a balloon. In the very center of its body is a yellow tape-like "X", which contains its small mouth in the very center. Located on either side of the "X" are its small, black eyes. A white mass of fluff that resembles a cloud sits on top of Drifloon\'s head.\n\nDue to its aimless drifting, this species is known as "Signpost for Wandering Spirits". It has been known to steal children that mistake it for a regular balloon. However, due to its light weight, it can be resisted easily and is often pulled around. Although created by lost spirits of Pokémon and people, [[DP028|as seen in the anime]], it can be friendly and helpful. It prefers to reside in damp, humid locations and can expand or shrink to express its feelings.\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Marnie Drifloon.png|thumb|left|220px|Drifloon in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\n====[[Fantina\'s Drifloon]]====\n[[Fantina]] owns a Drifloon, which debuted in \'\'[[DP093|Playing The Leveling Field!]]\'\'. It evolved into Drifblim while battling [[Ash\'s Pikachu]] in the same episode.\n\n====Other====\nDrifloon debuted in \'\'[[DP028|Drifloon on the Wind!]]\'\', where they were used by [[Marnie and Paige]] for transport. Marnie owned three and Paige owned one.\n\nMultiple Drifloon appeared in [[PK18]], where Pikachu and his friends grabbed on to them while escaping from {{MTR}} and his cronies. Meowth\'s group was later forced to hold on to more after being blasted off by a {{p|Registeel}}.\n\nA Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[DP076|A Full Course Tag Battle!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Kylie]]. It was used alongside [[Roman]]\'s {{p|Girafarig}} in a [[Multi Battle|Tag Battle]] against [[Dawn\'s Piplup]] and [[May\'s Blaziken]]. Drifloon was ultimately defeated by a combination of Piplup\'s {{m|Bubble Beam}} and Blaziken\'s {{m|Fire Spin}}.\n\nMultiple Drifloon appeared in [[PK20]], where Pikachu and his friends grabbed on to them while pursuing a {{p|Murkrow}} that had taken a large diamond ring piece.\n\nMultiple Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[XY041|Foggy Pokémon Orienteering!]]\'\'. They were used by {{Ash}} to hop across a gorge safely in order to reach {{an|Bonnie}}, who was sleeping on the other side.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nMultiple Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[M10|The Rise of Darkrai]]\'\'.\n\nA Drifloon appeared in [[James]]\'s fantasy in \'\'[[DP050|Tag! We\'re It...!]]\'\'.\n\nA Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[DP088|Camping It Up!]]\'\'.\n\nA Drifloon briefly appeared in \'\'[[DP176|Coming Full-Festival Circle!]]\'\'. It was among the Pokémon listening to [[Nando]] as he played his music.\n\nTwo Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[XY001|Kalos, Where Dreams and Adventures Begin!]]\'\'.\n\nFour {{pkmn|Trainer}}s\' Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\'.\n\nA student\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM002|The Guardian\'s Challenge!]]\'\'. It appeared again in the [[Banned episodes|banned episode]] [[SM064]].\n\nTwo Trainers\' Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM006|A Shocking Grocery Run!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM017|Crystal-Clear Sleuthing!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM040|Balloons, Brionne, and Belligerence!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM050|Faba\'s Revenge!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM060|Getting a Jump on the Competition!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM072|Sours for the Sweet!]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM081|A Young Royal Flame Ignites!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM083|Dummy, You Shrunk the Kids!]]\'\'.\n\nA Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM087|Filling the Light with Darkness!]]\'\', during a fantasy of a story from the past. It reappeared in a similar fashion during \'\'[[SM089|The Prism Between Light and Darkness!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM090|Securing the Future!]]\'\', where it joined the rest of [[Alola]] in showering {{DL|Light trio (anime)|Necrozma}} with light so it could return to its {{DL|List of Pokémon with form differences|Necrozma|normal form}}.\n\nMultiple Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM094|A Haunted House for Everyone!]]\'\' as illusions created by a {{p|Mismagius}}.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[SM128|League Offenders and Defenders!]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in [[SM140]].\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in [[SM141]].\n\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Animedexheader|Sinnoh}}\n{{Animedexbody|DP028|Drifloon|Dawn\'s Pokédex|Drifloon, the Balloon Pokémon. Drifloon is filled with air and can either expand or shrink to express its feelings. It also likes damp weather.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|\'\'Diamond & Pearl\'\'|Sinnoh}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Drifloon Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Drifloon in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Darkrai Mission Story: Pokémon Ranger Vatonage - the Comic manga===\nA Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[PRV1|A Fresh Start]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl manga===\nA Drifloon appeared in [[PDP07]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nDrifloon debuted in \'\'[[PS343|Honey for Combee]]\'\', under the ownership of the manager of the [[Valley Windworks]]. {{adv|Diamond}}, {{adv|Pearl}}, and {{adv|Platinum}} encountered it there.\n\nA Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[PS423|Tackling Togekiss]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[PS432|The Final Dimensional Duel II]]\'\'.\n\nA student\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[PS530|Movie Panic]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Drifloon appeared in \'\'[[PASM04|The Decision and the Tournament of Six]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Diamond and Pearl Adventure! manga===\nA Drifloon appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[DPAS1|Deoxys, The Phantom Pokémon! (Part 1)]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Pocket Monsters manga===\nA Drifloon appeared in [[PMDP33]].\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Drifloon (TCG)}}\n\n==Other appearances==\n===[[Super Smash Bros. Brawl]]===\nIn the {{st|Pokémon Stadium 2}} stage, a Drifloon can be seen floating on the {{t|Flying}} Terrain.\n\n====Trophy information====\n\'\'"A Balloon Pokémon that appears each Friday at the Valley Windworks in the Sinnoh region. It\'s round and cute, but it has a dreadful side too, as it attempts to drag children into the underworld by their hands. It likes damp, humid seasons. If it\'s on the verge of fainting in battle, it will counterattack by self-destructing. It evolves into Drifblim."\'\'\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=Ghost|type2=Flying}}\n