 Group]].\n** They are also the only {{type|Flying}} Pokémon and the only {{type|Ghost}} Pokémon in the Fluctuating Experience Group.\n\n===Origin===\nDrifloon are based on {{wp|balloon}}s. They also resemble {{wp|Ctenophora|comb jellies}}, specifically {{wp|tentaculata}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nDrifloon is a combination of \'\'drift\'\' and \'\'balloon\'\'.\n\nFuwante may be a combination of ふわふわ \'\'fuwa fuwa\'\' (\'\'soft\'\', \'\'airy\'\' and \'\'light\'\', or an {{wp|onomatopoeia}} for \'\'floating\'\'), 風船 \'\'fūsen\'\' (balloon), and 不安定 \'\'fuantei\'\' (unstable).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Ghost|type2=Flying\n|ja=フワンテ \'\'Fuwante\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|ふわふわ \'\'fuwa fuwa\'\'|soft, airy and light, onomatopoeia for floating}}, {{tt|風船 \'\'fūsen\'\'|balloon}}, and {{tt|不安定 \'\'fuantei\'\'|unstable}}\n|de=Driftlon|demeaning=From \'\'Drift\'\' and \'\'{{tt|Ballon|balloon}}\'\'\n|fr=Baudrive|frmeaning=From \'\'{{tt|baudruche|balloon}}\'\' and \'\'{{tt|dérive|drift}}\'\'\n|es=Drifloon|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|it=Drifloon|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=흔들풍손 \'\'Hundlpungson\'\'|komeaning=Combination of {{tt|흔들다 \'\'heundeulda\'\'|to shake or wave}} and a play on {{tt|풍선 \'\'pungseon\'\'|balloon}} and {{tt|손 \'\'son\'\'|hand}}.\n|zh_cmn=飄飄球 \'\'Piāo Piāo Qiú\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=Literally "Lightly floating balloon". {{tt|球|ball}} is derived from {{tt|氣球 \'\'Qì\u200bqiú\'\'|balloon}}.\n|ru=Дрифлун \'\'Driflun\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n<br clear="left">\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Fantina\'s Drifblim|Fantina\'s Drifloon]]\n\n==External links==\n\n{{-}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Ghost|type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Ghost|prevnum=424|prev=Ambipom|nextnum=426|next=Drifblim}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[de:Driftlon]]\n[[es:Drifloon]]\n[[fr:Baudrive]]\n[[it:Drifloon]]\n[[ja:フワンテ]]\n[[zh:飘飘球]]'}